SIMPLE: indifferency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indifferency
<hw>In*dif"fer*en*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Absence of
interest in, or influence from, anything; unconcernedness; equilibrium;
indifferentism; indifference.</def> <rj><au>Gladstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To give ourselves to a detestable <qex>indifferency</qex> or
neutrality in this cause.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Moral liberty . . . does not, after all, consist in a power of
<qex>indifferency</qex>, or in a power of choosing without regard to
motives.</q> <rj><qau>Hazlitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indifferent</ent>⟦br⟧
